all>\n*[[Jack Weston]] <small>(10-20-73)</small>\n{{div col end}}\n\n===Season 8 (1974\u20131975)===\n{{div col|colwidth=18em}}\n*[[Alan Alda]] <small>(12-21-74)</small>\n*[[James Coco]] <small>(9-28-74)</small>\n*[[Buddy Ebsen]] <small>(3-08-75)</small>\n*[[Rock Hudson]] <small>(2-15-75)</small>\n*[[Janet Jackson]] <small>(1-25-75)</small>\n*[[Alan King (comedian)|Alan King]] <small>(11-02-74)</small>\n*[[Kenneth Mars]] <small>(11-09-74)</small>\n*[[The Pointer Sisters]] <small>(9-28-74)</small>\n*[[Wayne Rogers]] <small>(3-08-75)</small>\n*[[Telly Savalas]] <small>(10-12-74)</small>\n*[[Phil Silvers]] <small>(3-29-75)</small>\n*[[Maggie Smith]] <small>(11-23-74)</small>\n*[[Jean Stapleton]] <small>(3-29-75)</small>\n*[[Sally Struthers]] <small>(3-22-75)</small>\n*[[Nancy Walker]] <small>(2-15-75)</small>\n*[[Lena Zavaroni]] <small>(11-02-74)</small>\n{{div col end}}\n\n===Season 9 (1975\u20131976)===\n{{div col|colwidth=18em}}\n*[[Sammy Davis Jr.]] <small>(9-20-75)</small>\n*[[Emmett Kelly]] <small>(1-24-76)</small>\n*[[Shirley MacLaine]] <small>(10-04-75)</small>\n*[[Rita Moreno]] <small>(1-03-76)</small>\n*[[Dick Van Dyke]] <small>(2-21-76)</small>\n*[[Jessica Walter]] <small>(12-13-75)</small>\n*[[Betty White]] <small>(11-22-75)</small>\n*[[Joanne Woodward]] <small>(2-14-76)</small>\n{{div col end}}\n\n===Season 10 (1976\u20131977)===\n{{div col|colwidth=18em}}\n*[[Glen Campbell]] <small>(1-15-77)</small>\n*[[Madeline Kahn]] <small>(10-16-76)</small>\n*[[Hal Linden]] <small>(3-05-77)</small>\n*[[Neil Sedaka]] <small>(3-19-77)</small>\n*[[Dinah Shore]] <small>(11-13-76)</small>\n*[[Ben Vereen]] <small>(2-26-77)</small>\n{{div col end}}\n\n===Season 11 (1977\u20131978)===\n{{div col|colwidth=18em}}\n*[[Captain and Tennille]] <small>(1-28-78)</small>\n*[[Natalie Cole]] <small>(2-04-78)</small>\n*[[Nancy Dussault]] <small>(10-15-77)</small>\n*[[Steve Martin]] <small>(3-04-78)</small>\n*[[James Stewart]] <small>(3-29-78)</small>\n{{div col end}}\n\n==Legacy==\nConsidering her large body of work, and due in great part to this TV show, Burnett received [[Kennedy Center Honors]] in 2003, and was awarded the [[Mark Twain Prize for American Humor]] in October 2013.<ref>{{cite news| url=https://www.cbsnews.com/8301-207_162-57585492/carol-burnett-to-win-top-u.s-humor-prize-in-dc/ | title=Carol Burnett to win top U.S. humor prize in DC| work=CBS News| date=May 21, 2013| accessdate=2015-03-11| agency=[[Associated Press]]}}</ref>\n\nIn 2009, ''[[TV Guide]]'' ranked \"Went with the Wind\" number 53 on its list of the 100 Greatest Episodes.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://rev-views.blogspot.com/2009/06/tv-guides-top-100-episodes.html|title=TV Guide's Top 100 Episodes|publisher=Rev/Views|accessdate=July 4, 2016}}</ref>\n\nOn September 13, 2016, Burnett released her memoir about the show titled ''[[In Such Good Company|In Such Good Company: Eleven Years of Laughter, Mayhem, and Fun in the Sandbox]]''. The book, full of anecdotes about the 1967\u20131978 variety series, covers the history of how Burnett created the show, how she cast her co-stars, the co-star she once fired (and quickly rehired), and all of the show's memorable characters.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/entertainment/books/carol-burnett-is-so-glad-we-had-this-time-together/2016/09/08/0901a8b2-7457-11e6-b786-19d0cb1ed06c_story.html?noredirect=on|title=Carol Burnett relives show\u2019s comedic genius with \u2018In Such Good Company\u2019|last=Henderson|first=Amy|work=[[The Washington Post]]|date=2016-09-09|accessdate=2018-07-31}}</ref> The audio format of the book, which she narrated, won a [[Grammy Award]] for Best Spoken Word Album.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.grammy.com/grammys/artists/carol-burnett|title=Artist Carol Burnett|website=www.grammy.com|accessdate=July 31, 2018}}</ref>\n\n==Home media==\nIn the early 2000s, certain full-length episodes of ''The Carol Burnett Show'' were released on VHS and DVD by [[Columbia House]] on a subscription basis (now discontinued). [[Guthy-Renker]] released another DVD collection, ''The Carol Burnett Show Collector's Edition''.\n\nIn August 2012, [[Time\u2013Life]] released ''The Carol Burnett Show - The Ultimate Collection'' on DVD in Region 1. This 22-disc set features 50 episodes from the series, selected by Burnett. It also contains bonus features, including interviews with the cast, featurettes, sketches that were never aired, and a 24-page commemorative booklet.\n\nIn August 2015, Time\u2013Life released ''The Carol Burnett Show - The Lost Episodes'' on DVD in Region 1. This 22-disc set features 45 episodes from the series' first five years (1967\u201372), selected by Burnett. It also contains bonus features, including interviews with the cast, featurettes, and a 24-page commemorative booklet.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.tvshowsondvd.com/news/Carol-Burnett-The-Lost-Episodes/21091 |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2015-08-04 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150804062334/http://www.tvshowsondvd.com/news/Carol-Burnett-The-Lost-Episodes/21091 |archivedate=August 4, 2015 |df=mdy-all }}</ref> Previously, due to an ongoing legal battle with the production company Bob Banner Associates, the episodes from those seasons had never appeared in syndication nor been released on home media.{{dubious|date=August 2015}}<ref>{{cite news| title=Carol Burnett Sued In Dispute Over Copyright And TV Show Revenue| url=https://www.deadline.com/2012/11/carol-burnett-sued-in-dispute-over-copyright-and-tv-show-revenue/| date=November 21, 2012| website=[[Deadline Hollywood]]| accessdate=2015-03-11}}</ref>{{Failed verification|date=August 2015}}\n\n==Nielsen ratings/broadcast schedule==\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|-\n!  Season  !!  Rank <ref>{{cite web|title=TV Ratings|url=http://www.classictvhits.com/tvratings/index.htm|accessdate=February 17, 2013}}</ref>  !!  Rating  !!  Time slot \n|-\n| 1 ([[1967\u201368 United States network television schedule|